cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with computer vision techniques for aligning scanned or camera-captured document images for information extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes Optical character recognition (OCR) engine for finding character-based keypoints, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for aligning document images, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
